# my.onUnhandledRejection

2022-07-03 18:44

Listen for the _unhandledrejection_ event. The _unhandledrejection_ event is triggered when a JavaScript `Promise` that has no rejection handler is rejected. The triggered time of the callback for the _unhandledrejection_ event and required parameters are the same with those of the [onUnhandledRejection()](https://miniprogram.gcash.com/docs/miniprogram_gcash/mpdev/framework_app_register-mini-program#mGRwY) method.

## Sample code

copy

```javascript
//.js
App({
  onShow(options) {
    my.onUnhandledRejection((res) => {
      console.log(res.reason);
      console.log(res.promise);
    });
  }
})
```

## Parameters

|     |     |     |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Property** | **Type** | **Description** |
| callback | Function | The _unhandledrejection_ event is triggered when a JavaScript `Promise` that has no rejection handler is rejected. |

### Callback function

|     |     |     |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Property** | **Type** | **Description** |
| reason | String | Rejection reason, which usually is the error object. |
| promise | Promise | The rejected Promise object. |
